<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="434" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="40.[782,1374,1988,2411]" pageId="40" pageNumber="434">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Merriam" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[786,1040,2221,2254]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Cryptotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="40" pageNumber="434" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="peregrinus">Cryptotis peregrinus</taxonomicName>
was considered a subspecies of C. mexicanus until N. Woodman and R. M. Timm in 1999 recognized it as a distinct species. L. Guevara and F. A. Cervantes in 2014 and A. B. Baird and col-
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[166,1375,2421,3475]" pageId="40" pageNumber="434">
leagues in 2018 found that C. peregrinus was in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Merriam" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[882,1038,2421,2450]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Cryptotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="40" pageNumber="434" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="goldmani">C. goldmani</taxonomicName>
group, with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Merriam" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[1219,1375,2421,2450]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Cryptotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="40" pageNumber="436" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="goldmani">C. goldmani</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Merriam" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[234,362,2456,2489]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Cryptotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="40" pageNumber="434" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alticola">C. alticola</taxonomicName>
, and sister to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Merriam" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[560,715,2456,2489]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Cryptotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="40" pageNumber="436" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="goldmani">C. goldmani</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
